header.gameNote: UCF HOLIDAY CLASSIC AT ORLANDO FL

article.headline: Long Island U. 95, Texas-Pan American 83
article.story: ORLANDO (AP) -- Kellen Allen posted 22 points on 9-of-10 shooting as Long Island advanced to the title game of the University of Central Florida Holiday Classic with a 95-83 win over Texas-Pan American on Sunday. Long Island (9-3) finished with six players in double-figures, while UTPA (7-10) was paced by Paul Stoll's career-high 24 points. The victory extended Long Island's winning streak to five games. Early in the first half, UTPA secured a 9-0 run over a span of 5:14 to take a 22-17 lead. Long Island responded by scoring 11 unanswered points en route to entering the break with a slim 35-34 edge. Long Island drained its first six 3-pointers in the second stanza to jump out to a 59-46 cushion. The Blackbirds then cruised the rest of the way for the 12-point triumph.
